Description:
Arguably The Most Affordable Home in Coburg
Open to improvement whilst presenting an exceedingly rare opportunity this three bedroom single fronted Victorian home, is located in a highly sought-after pocket of Coburg, just a short walk from Coburg North Primary, O'Hea Street Bakery, local shops and public transport.
Offering an abundance of original features including high ornate ceilings and wrought iron fretwork; this amazing property is ready to be restored to its former glory, or demolish & redesign (STCA).
Reconfigure the spacious interior to boost the considerably proportioned living spaces comprising large lounge room; which flows through an archway to sizable kitchen/meals and an internal laundry easily adapted to extend the existing kitchen area or enlarge the dimensions of the bathroom.
A peaceful rear courtyard provides privacy and quietude with the added utility of a workshop and shed on premises.
Huge bedrooms include a toilet ensuite to the master; with everything in place for a sympathetic makeover.
Includes a 600mm Euromaid oven, ceiling fans, split system air conditioning, and Vulcan wall heater.
Offering immense appeal for renovators and investors alike, the excellent position of this property also allows easy access to the CBD via CityLink.
Insights: 11 Collins Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Outstanding views in a secure and stylish setting
Peacefully positioned overlooking the manicured lawns of the West Coburg Bowling Club, this immaculate modern townhouse makes the most of its sought-after setting enjoying abundant north light, a quiet ambience and verdant views towards the city skyline. Presented as-new with a stylish contemporary look and high-quality appointments, this secure and secluded home in a boutique block of 3 offers an outstanding low-upkeep lifestyle in a convenient pocket close to Sydney Road shops, cafes, restaurants and Coburg station. Features include 2 smart bedrooms with built-in robes, spacious living and dining room, entertainment balcony with views, excellent stone kitchen with stainless-steel appliances, twin-shower bathroom, powder room, laundry, heating/cooling, alarm, video intercom, polished hardwood floors and remote-control garage.
Insights: 2/40 Linsey Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Contemporary Choice In Central Position
An easy choice in a central location south of Bell Street and close to trains, trams, shops, Coburg Market, parks and cafes, this contemporary two bedroom residence features a flowing kitchen/meals/living with stainless steel appliances enhanced by stone surfaces and soft close cabinetry. Stylish, secure and sunlit it has double bedrooms with BIRs, a shining central bathroom and Euro laundry. A sliding glass stacker links the living zone to a covered balcony and appealing extras include a video intercom, heating/cooling, storage and secure covered OSP with rear access. Easy maintenance further recommends this well connected home to investors and aspiring residents.

Description:
'Rosalie'
A family haven in a well connected locale, 'Rosalie' is a four bedroom, two bathroom Californian Bungalow featuring a tranquil covered entertainer's deck in a landscaped rear garden flaunting a tropical feel. Alive with character enhanced by high ceilings, polished floorboards, decorative fireplaces and timber fretwork, she presents an attractively proportioned kitchen/meals/family with stainless steel appliances and an array of windows welcoming in peaceful views. Sizeable bedrooms include three with built-in robes, gleaming bathrooms include a chic and modern main bathroom, and there's ducted heating, evaporative cooling, attic storage, a garden shed and off street parking for two. Trains, trams, local shops, Sydney Road and Coburg Lake are all within moments and several schools nearby.

Description:
Family Proportions in the Perfect Position
The beauty of its period profile endures, creating a classical introduction to this home's abundant present appeal. At the end of an inviting hallway, a great sense of space and comfort is created by generous family lounge and dining zone that features an efficient Coonara slow combustion heater, accompanied by wraparound kitchen where stainless-steel appliances lift the modern profile. Polished floorboards and built-in-robes complements the three bedrooms, each beneath original high ceilings, that share gleaming bathroom. Significant, grassy garden proportions beckon to the rear, enhanced by open-air entertainer's deck and an ideal context for extension if/when desired. The combination of gas ducted heating/evaporative cooling and security system complete an engaging residence, with convenient off-street car parking, surrounded by attractions such as Sydney Rd's shops and cafes, schools, local parks, Coburg Station and Citylink accessibility.
Insights: 16 Deakin Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Boutique Living In The Heart Of Coburg!
Superb chance to secure your place in a stunning boutique block of seven, this distinctive unit delivers high-quality, low-maintenance living at its absolute best.
Complete with its own street frontage and private entrance, the home's light-filled interior comprises two double bedrooms (both with robes), stylish master ensuite and main central bathroom, spacious open-plan living/dining area complemented by a well-appointed kitchen with soft-close drawers, stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher.
Other stand-out features include split-system heating and cooling, stone benchtops and vanities, video intercom, laundry facilities, plus a private courtyard and secure garage space with remote-control.
South of Bell Street, it's walking distance to Coburg Station and shopping centre, Sydney Road cafes and trams. Simply move in and start living! Inspection By Appointment - Enquire Today!
NB. Regarding indicated Price - Please understand, particularly on the more 'popular' properties or in a 'hot' property market that more than one buyer may be interested in the same property. When that happens, all buyers will be given EQUAL OPPORTUNITY TO MAKE THEIR BEST OFFERS.

Description:
Traditions that Translate to Today
A graceful Californian bungalow advantaged by an address within the Strathmore College zone, this home's gently renovated spaces represent a beautiful balance of period authenticity and present-day appeal. The classical character of verandah and central entrance hall creates an alluring introduction to the two bedrooms, each featuring built-in-robes, and formal lounge defined by the warmth of the original open fireplace. A modern bathroom accompanies the kitchen and dining domain where sleek stainless-steel appliances meet a beautiful brick hearth while to the rear decked dimensions deliver a sensational backdrop. Hallmarks of the period include high ceilings, picture tails and a handsome street presence further complement the comfort of ducted heating and the convenience of parking for multiple cars in a location that's just steps to Melville Rd trams and a short stroll from Coburg Station and shopping on Sydney Rd.

Description:
'Valros': beautifully situated tranquillity
Superbly located in a wonderfully connected position a stroll to an exciting array of amenities, 'Valros' is a handsome five bedroom Californian Bungalow and a surprisingly tranquil haven featuring a serene rear deck and garden. Presenting: lounge (or fifth bedroom) and kitchen/dining/family with 900mm Belling stove, dishwasher, timber cabinetry, slate flooring, wood heater, plantation shutters and six doors opening to the deck welcoming in leafy views. High ceilings, rosettes, timber fretwork, leadlight, OFPs, polished floorboards and verandah with pressed metal ceiling. Chic bathroom with deep bath and frameless shower, heating, cooling and OSP with electronic access to rear ROW. Stroll to trains, trams, Post Office Hotel, Coburg Market and cafes. Nearby bike path access to the city.

Description:
Windows On The Park

Description:
Memories of pomodoro & vino in The Grove - 981sqm (approx.)
This pristine family home is steeped in love and must be the most immaculately presented house in Coburg. Not only is it positioned in one of the most prestigious pockets in Melbourne, this elegant brick residence was once the highest priced home in Coburg back in 1984. Now on the market for the first time in a generation it is a rare opportunity for true family-sized living, for families needing room to grow. As soon as you step foot through the front door you will be blown away by the stunning character and grand proportions it has to offer. The versatile floor plan includes three bedrooms, two with built in robes, and the huge master suite, a stunning original bathroom complete with bathtub, mirrored make up counter and vanity adjoining a separate shower, separate WC and large separate laundry. This property also offers a separate spacious formal lounge with original fireplace and pendant light feature as well as a log heater. To the rear of the home a vast open plan kitchen/meals and living area, the kitchen showcasing stainless steel appliances, stone bench tops, glass splashback and ample storage. Beyond the floor to ceiling glass sliding door a paved undercover entertainer's area and an immense north facing rear yard that accommodates a four car garage with additional kitchenette, wine cellar, work shop with additional storage, outdoor wood fire oven and fire burner next to a second workshop. This residence is a real entertainer's delight and the perfect setting for a growing family. Within easy reach to Sydney Road and Nicholson Street shops, eateries and trams, local primary and secondary schools as well as surrounding parklands. This home truly is a vintage masterpiece.
Insights: 41 The Grove, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

On its own separately-titled block with no shared land, this two-storey townhouse presents a sensational inner-urban lifestyle opportunity with its contemporary class, surprising space and unbeatable convenience. Bathed in natural light, the home's impressive interior comprises two bedrooms (large master) both with mirrored robes, stylish central bathroom and additional powder room (second WC). Description:
Versatile Style in a Picture-Perfect Setting
In a blissfully quiet neighbourhood with parkland across the road, this two-storey home is sure to make an impression with its surprisingly spacious floorplan, quality enhancements and abundance of natural light throughout. Meticulously-detailed interior comprises three genuinely large bedrooms (master with WIR, two with BIRs), stylish ensuite and main bathroom, front lounge with park views through to the open living/dining area accompanied by a granite-bench kitchen with tiled splashbacks and stainless steel appliances. Other features of the home include ducted heating/refrigerated cooling, new carpets and LED lighting, data cabling, double-glazed windows all-round, laundry and third WC, plus undercover balcony to enjoy the leafy outlook, wonderfully private back garden, internally-accessed garage (r/c) and additional driveway parking. Walking distance to Coburg High School, it's also close to Coburg Lake and Merri Creek trails, Coburg Station and renowned shopping centre, Sydney Road trams, cafes and restaurants. Inner-urban perfection! Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Contemporary Chic City Sanctuary - PLEASE ENTER VIA PARK STREET
Enjoy a classy, carefree lifestyle from the comfort and security of this ultra stylish two bedroom residence situated a stone's throw from colourful Sydney Road cafés, shops and city transport. Inside generous open plan living/dining and entry spaces are highlighted by extra high ceilings, quality craftsmanship and high end finishes, meanwhile glass stacker doors open wide to reveal a large courtyard ideal for wining, dining and entertaining alfresco. Clever design is expressed in a streamline kitchen displaying stone benches, slick two tone cabinetry and stainless steel appliances. Two beautifully appointed bedrooms present oversize built-in-robes and share a fully tiled luxe bathroom. Features split-systems, powder room, intercom/alarm, storage and off street parking with automated garaging/direct home entry. Nearby are Coburg station, markets, schools and parklands.

Description:
Location, Luxury and Brand-New Style
Wonderfully quiet yet incredibly convenient, this stunning new townhouse presents an idyllic low-maintenance lifestyle with its clever design, first-class features and immediate access to everything that counts. Bathed in natural light, the home's meticulously detailed interior boasts three bedrooms (large master) all with built-in robes, deluxe ensuite, equally-stylish main bathroom and additional powder room (third WC). Add to this a well-appointed kitchen with breakfast bar, soft-close drawers, Baumatic cooking appliances and dishwasher, as well as an expansive open-plan living/dining area with stacker doors revealing a sunny terrace. Other highlights include split-system heating and cooling (all bedrooms and living area), ducted vacuum, stone benchtops throughout, hardwood floors, alarm and video intercom, plus a large laundry, under-stair storeroom, courtyard and double garage (r/c) with internal entry. In a prime location walking distance to Batman Station and Sydney Road trams, it's also close to primary and secondary schools, Coburg Lake, popular cafes and vibrant shopping precincts.
